00:45:05.568 --> 00:45:08.228
that drives a lot of our behaviors with money.

1104
00:45:08.228 --> 00:45:11.948
He talked about that in some of his interviews.

1105
00:45:11.948 --> 00:45:14.188
That feeling of being lonely.

1106
00:45:14.188 --> 00:45:16.728
And so even with all of that money,

1107
00:45:16.728 --> 00:45:19.848
and all of that success, you know,

1108
00:45:19.848 --> 00:45:21.408
this may have been someone who

1109
00:45:21.408 --> 00:45:23.508
really felt a lot of spiritual depletion.

1110
00:45:23.508 --> 00:45:26.088
That really set him up for all of these behaviors.

1111
00:45:26.088 --> 00:45:28.568
So, I felt a lot of empathy and compassion.

1112
00:45:28.568 --> 00:45:30.428
And I also thought, you know,

1113
00:45:30.428 --> 00:45:31.788
there's more to the story here.

1114
00:45:31.788 --> 00:45:33.128
So I was thrilled that they let me

1115
00:45:33.128 --> 00:45:34.448
use that story in the book.

1116
00:45:34.448 --> 00:45:36.208
Because I thought, here's an example,

1117
00:45:36.208 --> 00:45:39.048
we think of people that don't make very much money,

1118
00:45:39.048 --> 00:45:41.448
we think of a certain type of person

1119
00:45:41.448 --> 00:45:43.188
that has money problems,

1120
00:45:43.188 --> 00:45:46.088
but we see the Michael Jacksons, we see the movie stars,

1121
00:45:46.088 --> 00:45:49.428
we see the athletes, we see the lottery winners.

1122
00:45:49.428 --> 00:45:51.748
We see them get large sums of money,

1123
00:45:51.748 --> 00:45:53.368
sometimes quite suddenly,

1124
00:45:53.368 --> 00:45:55.548
and sometimes they work for it over time.

1125
00:45:55.548 --> 00:45:58.508
However, they can be quite ill equipped to handle it,

1126
00:45:58.508 --> 00:46:02.448
and if they don't have a sense of who they are,

1127
00:46:02.448 --> 00:46:06.168
they're really at risk for having end up being

1128
00:46:06.168 --> 00:46:08.648
more of a curse than a blessing.

1129
00:46:08.648 --> 00:46:10.088
And then there's a lot of people who

1130
00:46:10.088 --> 00:46:11.588
have money and do great things.

1131
00:46:11.588 --> 00:46:13.428
So, money is a good thing.

1132
00:46:13.428 --> 00:46:14.988
I don't want anyone to think I'm saying

1133
00:46:14.988 --> 00:46:16.788
money is not a good thing.

1134
00:46:16.788 --> 00:46:18.688
However, you know, we have the people that

1135
00:46:18.688 --> 00:46:21.368
have a lot of money and do great things in the world,

1136
00:46:21.368 --> 00:46:23.608
and then we have a lot of people that go on a very

1137
00:46:23.608 --> 00:46:26.618
self destructive path when they have that kind of money.

1138
00:46:26.618 --> 00:46:27.889
[Regina] And if could almost equate

1139
00:46:27.889 --> 00:46:29.529
the term money with energy.

1140
00:46:29.529 --> 00:46:32.089
That we deserve the energetic support,

1141
00:46:32.089 --> 00:46:35.969
we should have the energetic support that we deserve

1142
00:46:35.969 --> 00:46:39.029
in life, and yet we have to define what that is.

1143
00:46:39.029 --> 00:46:39.889
<v ->What that is.</v>

1144
00:46:39.889 --> 00:46:41.689
And we wanna have role models.

1145
00:46:41.689 --> 00:46:43.409
I really recommend that people

1146
00:46:43.409 --> 00:46:45.889
read biographies of their role models.

1147
00:46:45.889 --> 00:46:48.229
And, of course, a role model for me

1148
00:46:48.229 --> 00:46:49.849
has always been Oprah Winfrey.

1149
00:46:49.849 --> 00:46:53.789
This is someone that absolutely created her passion.

1150
00:46:53.789 --> 00:46:56.229
And she's just retired from the

1151
00:46:56.229 --> 00:46:58.149
25 years of being on the show.

1152
00:46:58.149 --> 00:47:01.849
This is one of the wealthiest women in the world.

1153
00:47:01.849 --> 00:47:05.189
And, she has, she enjoys her life,

1154
00:47:05.189 --> 00:47:07.469
and she makes no qualms about it,

1155
00:47:07.469 --> 00:47:08.809
she doesn't apologize about it.

1156
00:47:08.809 --> 00:47:11.409
But she also gives a lot of money away.

1157
00:47:11.409 --> 00:47:13.709
Has great satisfaction from that.

1158
00:47:13.709 --> 00:47:14.949
And so--

1159
00:47:14.949 --> 00:47:16.529
[Regina] She loves her work.

1160
00:47:16.529 --> 00:47:19.509
<v ->She loves her work, and she's helped</v>

1161
00:47:19.509 --> 00:47:21.189
changed a lot of people's lives.

1162
00:47:21.189 --> 00:47:24.189
So she has the satisfaction of a career,

1163
00:47:24.189 --> 00:47:26.129
where she makes good money,

1164
00:47:26.129 --> 00:47:29.029
but she also has that satisfaction of knowing that she's

1165
00:47:29.029 --> 00:47:31.229
really made a difference in a lot of people's lives.

1166
00:47:31.229 --> 00:47:33.629
To me it doesn't get better than that.

1167
00:47:33.629 --> 00:47:35.669
[Regina] It doesn't, and that is a key for a lot of people.

1168
00:47:35.669 --> 00:47:37.449
They're slogging long, doing what they

1169
00:47:37.449 --> 00:47:39.549
don't like to do to survive so that they can

1170
00:47:39.549 --> 00:47:41.449
spend a little time doing what they do what to do.

1171
00:47:41.449 --> 00:47:43.109
And sometimes the thing you love doing

1172
00:47:43.109 --> 00:47:45.129
is not going to be what makes you money.

1173
00:47:45.129 --> 00:47:46.969
There is an interesting balance in there.

1174
00:47:46.969 --> 00:47:48.609
Dan Melman wrote a book on it,

1175
00:47:48.609 --> 00:47:50.729
called The Four Purposes of Life, which addresses that.

1176
00:47:50.729 --> 00:47:52.789
Does your passion always have

1177
00:47:52.789 --> 00:47:56.089
to be the way in which you earn your bread, so to speak.

1178
00:47:56.089 --> 00:47:58.509
They may not match up, but there are ways

1179
00:47:58.509 --> 00:48:03.409
to fill that creative and spiritual well within yourself,

1180
00:48:03.409 --> 00:48:07.269
so that the other is more exceptable, even.

1181
00:48:07.269 --> 00:48:09.289
It's going for a higher purpose, even if

1182
00:48:09.289 --> 00:48:11.409
it isn't maybe your dream job.

1183
00:48:11.409 --> 00:48:14.789
How do you rectify that, the way you look at it?

1184
00:48:14.789 --> 00:48:17.469
<v ->I think that one of the ways that people rectify it,</v>

1185
00:48:17.469 --> 00:48:19.409
you know, there is this misconception

1186
00:48:19.409 --> 00:48:22.049
that we're all going to find work that we

1187
00:48:22.049 --> 00:48:24.409
absolutely love and then the money will follow.

1188
00:48:24.409 --> 00:48:26.609
And that isn't true for everyone.

1189
00:48:26.609 --> 00:48:28.129
Now, I have a chapter in the book called,

1190
00:48:28.129 --> 00:48:31.129
Is your work working for you and the money isn't?

1191
00:48:31.129 --> 00:48:33.229
Is the money working for you and the work isn't?

1192
00:48:33.229 --> 00:48:35.129
Are neither working for you?

1193
00:48:35.129 --> 00:48:37.989
So, for people who have not been able

1194
00:48:37.989 --> 00:48:40.589
to find the work that they absolutely love,

1195
00:48:40.589 --> 00:48:43.349
it's very important then, that they are creating,

1196
00:48:43.349 --> 00:48:47.609
outside of their work, these interest that they have.

1197
00:48:47.609 --> 00:48:49.909
And these things that give their lives meaning.

1198
00:48:49.909 --> 00:48:51.909
So, I think it is a misconception

1199
00:48:51.909 --> 00:48:54.229
that do what we want and the money will follow.

1200
00:48:54.229 --> 00:48:56.849
But we can adjust, if we really are in a

1201
00:48:56.849 --> 00:48:58.909
very unhealthy work environment

1202
00:48:58.909 --> 00:49:00.809
then it is important to look at that.

1203
00:49:00.809 --> 00:49:02.529
And again, people can't look at that

1204
00:49:02.529 --> 00:49:04.449
if they are in survival mode with money.

