1207
00:49:11.967 --> 00:49:15.327
their finanacial situation, now they could entertain

1208
00:49:15.327 --> 00:49:18.766
this concept of right livelihood and their work.

1209
00:49:18.766 --> 00:49:21.806
And quite often, it was, no they could make their work

1210
00:49:21.806 --> 00:49:24.147
manageable and they could make the most out of it.

1211
00:49:24.147 --> 00:49:25.787
But it was with the rest of their life, then,

1212
00:49:25.787 --> 00:49:28.346
that they are going to meet this other need,

1213
00:49:28.346 --> 00:49:30.806
of their creativity and making sure that they are

1214
00:49:30.806 --> 00:49:33.146
making a difference in what's important to them.

1215
00:49:33.146 --> 00:49:35.067
[Regina] That makes perfect sense.

1216
00:49:35.067 --> 00:49:39.807
And this gets us to the story of enough.

1217
00:49:39.807 --> 00:49:42.929
For some people there isn't enough.

1218
00:49:42.929 --> 00:49:46.969
And they just have to acquire more and more and more.

1219
00:49:46.969 --> 00:49:49.374
Whether they're in a thing they love or not.

1220
00:49:49.374 --> 00:49:51.675
There is just no such thing as enough.

1221
00:49:51.675 --> 00:49:55.474
How do you define what is enough,

1222
00:49:55.474 --> 00:49:58.695
for you as an individual?

1223
00:49:58.695 --> 00:50:01.655
<v ->That's a fantastic question.</v>

1224
00:50:01.655 --> 00:50:04.254
There's an exercise I have in the book,

1225
00:50:04.254 --> 00:50:06.255
and I also do at workshops,

1226
00:50:06.255 --> 00:50:08.335
where I take people through a meditation

1227
00:50:08.335 --> 00:50:10.615
looking at what their earning ceilings are.

1228
00:50:10.615 --> 00:50:14.555
And what we do is, we go to different levels

1229
00:50:14.555 --> 00:50:16.635
and we start with a very low level

1230
00:50:16.635 --> 00:50:18.095
and then we get to a high level.

1231
00:50:18.095 --> 00:50:19.494
And you can see where people have

1232
00:50:19.494 --> 00:50:21.054
reached their earning ceiling.

1233
00:50:21.054 --> 00:50:22.495
You know their eyes will pop open,

1234
00:50:22.495 --> 00:50:23.915
or they'll start giggling, they feel

1235
00:50:23.915 --> 00:50:26.014
very uncomfortable in their body.

1236
00:50:26.014 --> 00:50:28.635
And in all the years that I've been doing this,

1237
00:50:28.635 --> 00:50:32.274
I've only had one person who realized

1238
00:50:32.274 --> 00:50:34.834
that she could be enough even if

1239
00:50:34.834 --> 00:50:38.274
she was at this very, very low income level.

1240
00:50:38.274 --> 00:50:41.975
Like I said, in all the, with all the people

1241
00:50:41.975 --> 00:50:43.575
I've done this with, it's only one.

1242
00:50:43.575 --> 00:50:46.795
And what she said is she would make her life enough.

1243
00:50:46.795 --> 00:50:50.055
She would look for other people in a similar situation.

1244
00:50:50.055 --> 00:50:53.294
She would look at sharing resources,

1245
00:50:53.294 --> 00:50:57.135
perhaps sharing a home, perhaps sharing cars,

1246
00:50:57.135 --> 00:51:00.214
perhaps putting gardens in and having,

1247
00:51:00.214 --> 00:51:03.095
she would just find other people in this situation.

1248
00:51:03.095 --> 00:51:06.524
And so, the big question for a lot of people,

1249
00:51:06.524 --> 00:51:11.475
and I feel that the other part of this that's important is,

1250
00:51:11.475 --> 00:51:16.474
if we know that we want to have a certain lifestyle.

1251
00:51:16.474 --> 00:51:18.274
And, let's say a school teacher, for example,

1252
00:51:18.274 --> 00:51:22.314
who doesn't make very much money, but they love their work.

1253
00:51:22.314 --> 00:51:26.654
There has to be a match between the money they make

1254
00:51:26.654 --> 00:51:29.034
and the lifestyle they choose.

1255
00:51:29.034 --> 00:51:31.634
Because otherwise, here they have work that they love,

1256
00:51:31.634 --> 00:51:33.254
but it's never going to be enough,

1257
00:51:33.254 --> 00:51:36.994
because they don't shop and they don't live

1258
00:51:36.994 --> 00:51:39.914
the lifestyle based on the salary that they have.

1259
00:51:39.914 --> 00:51:43.094
And so, that's one of the things about getting to enough,

1260
00:51:43.094 --> 00:51:45.114
is that if we do have work that we love,

1261
00:51:45.114 --> 00:51:49.254
then we have to adjust our lifestyle to meet that.

1262
00:51:49.254 --> 00:51:52.054
So, a school teacher, and I have someone

1263
00:51:52.054 --> 00:51:53.614
in mind thinking about that.

1264
00:51:53.614 --> 00:51:57.194
She shops at certain places and not others.

1265
00:51:57.194 --> 00:52:01.494
She feels rich because she absolutely loves what she does.

1266
00:52:01.494 --> 00:52:03.774
